%20sector%20may%20shed%20some%20light%20on%20the%20contrast%20in%20priority%20given%20to%20the%20large%20corporates%20and%20the%20Micro%2C%20Small%20and%20Medium%20Enterprises%20(MSMEs).%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20capital%20markets%20regulator%20reviews%20corporate%20borrowing%20limits%2C%20MSMEs%20grapple%20with%20loan%20rejection%20challenges.%20The%20developments%20come%20amid%20another%20news%20on%20the%20banking%20sector%20%E2%80%93%20that%20banks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbanks-wrote-off-rs-14-56-lakh-crore-since-2014-15-govt%5C%22%3Ehave%20written%20off%20bad%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20worth%20Rs%2014.56%20lakh%20crore%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20financial%20years%20starting%202014-15.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%2050%20wilful%20defaulters%20%E2%80%93%20including%20Gitanjali%20Gems%2C%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EEra%20Infra%20Engineering%20Limited%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EREI%20Agro%20Limited%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EABG%20Shipyard%20Limited%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20owe%20Rs%2087%2C295%20crore%20to%20banks%20and%20financial%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20who%20pays%20for%20cronyism%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbank-recap-end-indias-taxpayer-pays-cronyism%5C%22%3Ethe%20taxpayer.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fmodi-government-npas-loans-write-off-12-lakh-crore%5C%22%3EHow%20in%20First%20Eight%20Years%20of%20Modi%20Government%2C%20Nearly%20Rs%2012%20Lakh%20Crore%20%E2%80%98Disappeared%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERaising%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eborrowing%20threshold%20for%20large%20corporates%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Board%20of%20India%20(SEBI)%20on%20Thursday%2C%20August%2010%20proposed%20to%20raise%20the%20borrowing%20threshold%20for%20large%20corporates%20to%20Rs%20500%20crore%20from%20the%20current%20Rs%20100%20crore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20capital%20markets%20regulator%20has%20also%20proposed%20several%20other%20norms%20such%20as%20removing%20the%200.2%25%20penalty%20on%20large%20corporates%20for%20any%20shortfall%20in%20their%20incremental%20borrowings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20present%20norms%2C%20large%20corporates%20are%20required%20to%20raise%2025%25%20of%20their%20incremental%20borrowings%20in%20a%20financial%20year%20by%20issuing%20debt%20securities%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fregulator-sebi-proposes-to-ease-norms-for-borrowings-by-large-corporates-123081000876_1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20penalty%20of%200.2%25%20of%20the%20shortfall%20is%20to%20be%20levied%20in%20case%20of%20not%20meeting%20the%20threshold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20increasing%20the%20outstanding%20long-term%20borrowing%20threshold%20to%20Rs%20500%20crore%20or%20above%20for%20eligibility%20as%20a%20large%20corporate%2C%20SEBI%20has%20removed%20the%20requirement%20of%20credit%20rating%20for%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20current%20rules%2C%20large%20corporates%20are%20those%20that%20need%20to%20have%20an%20outstanding%20long-term%20borrowing%20of%20at%20least%20Rs%20100%20crore%3B%20a%20credit%20rating%20of%20%E2%80%98AA%E2%80%99%3B%20and%20a%20target%20to%20finance%20themselves%20with%20long-term%20borrowings%20(above%20one%20year).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaising%20funds%20from%20banks%20and%20financial%20institutions%20is%20a%20cost-effective%20option.%20Raising%20funds%20from%20debt%20securities%2C%20however%2C%20is%20costly%20because%20the%20borrowing%20cost%20is%20high%2C%20due%20to%20tightening%20liquidity%20and%20hikes%20in%20the%20benchmark%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%20one-third%20of%20the%20identified%20large%20corporates%20did%20not%20raise%20the%20minimum%2025%25%20of%20their%20incremental%20borrowings%20through%20issuance%20of%20debt%20securities%20in%20the%20financial%20year%202021-22%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fin.investing.com%2Fnews%2Fonethird-of-large-corporates-didnt-raise-25-of-borrowings-through-debt-securities-3766937%5C%22%3EIANS%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20large%20corporates%20are%20turning%20to%20large%20banks%20or%20foreign%20banks%20for%20their%20borrowing%20needs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Findustry%2Fbanking-finance%2Fmore-corporates-turn-to-large-private-banks-for-loans-report%2F3186895%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20a%20report%20from%20Coalition%20Greenwich%2C%20which%20is%20a%20division%20of%20CRISIL.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%202021%20to%202022%2C%20the%20share%20of%20Indian%20corporates%20working%20with%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20private%20sector%20banks%20for%20overall%20corporate%20banking%20services%20increased%20to%2038%25%20from%2033%25%20earlier.%20Over%20the%20same%20period%2C%20the%20share%20of%20corporates%20working%20with%20at%20least%20one%20large%20foreign%20bank%20climbed%20to%2021%25%20from%2018%25%20earlier%2C%20the%20report%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fmost-msmes-are-not-even-in-the-policy-net%5C%22%3EMost%20MSMEs%20Are%20Not%20Even%20in%20the%20Policy%20Net%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELoans%20to%20MSMEs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20bank%20credit%20growth%20to%20Micro%2C%20Small%20and%20Medium%20Enterprises%20(MSMEs)%20has%20decelerated%20on%20a%20year-on-year%20basis%20in%20the%20first%20three%20months%20of%20the%20current%20fiscal%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Fbank-credit-growth-to-msmes-decelerates-in-q1-rbi-data-2636894%5C%22%3EReserve%20Bank%20data%20showed.%3C%2Fa%3E%20This%20is%20because%20risk%20averse%20banks%20are%20reluctant%20to%20lend%20to%20small%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiz2Credit%20co-founder%20and%20CEO%20Rohit%20Arora%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fbusiness%2Fbank-credit-growth-to-msmes-decelerates-in-q1-rbi-data-news-308547%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20PTI%20that%20MSMEs%20in%20India%20are%20facing%20challenges%20in%20obtaining%20credit%20from%20banks%20and%20financial%20institutions%20due%20to%20factors%20like%20collateral%20requirements%2C%20limited%20credit%20history%20and%20high-interest%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMSMEs%20are%20the%20backbone%20of%20the%20economy%20in%20terms%20of%20employment%20and%20contribution%20to%20the%20GDP.%20These%20enterprise%20contribute%20around%2030%25%20to%20the%20GDP.%20Moreover%2C%20NITI%20Aayog%20CEO%20Amitabh%20Kant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fsmall-biz%2Fsme-sector%2Frole-of-msmes-crucial-for-india-to-become-a-5-trillion-economy-says-kant%2Farticleshow%2F88605491.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ehad%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20these%20business%20are%20crucial%20for%20India%20to%20become%20a%20%245%20trillion%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20MSMEs%20face%20the%20problems%20of%20access%20to%20long-term%20credit%2C%20delayed%20payments%20and%20heavy%20debt%2C%20every%20single%20day%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessworld.in%2Farticle%2FDelayed-Payments-Heavy-Debt-Indian-MSMEs-Fighting-A-Long-Battle%2F31-07-2023-485930%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%20%3Cem%3EBusinessWorld%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20told%20%3Cem%3EBW%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20rise%20in%20bad%20MSME%20loans%20in%20India%20is%20due%20to%20factors%20such%20as%20the%20impact%20of%20slowing%20exports%2C%20the%20slowdown%20in%20certain%20global%20markets%2C%20sectors%2C%20withdrawal%20of%20COVID-19%20concessions%20and%20rising%20interest%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20banks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fbanking%2Ffinance%2Fbanking%2Fbanks-reach-out-to-rbi-seek-easing-of-msme-bad-loan-rules%2Farticleshow%2F98923918.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ehad%20reached%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20seeking%20relaxation%20of%20bad%20loans%20norms%20for%20MSMEs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBanks%20want%20that%20a%20restructured%20MSME%20account%20under%20the%20COVID-19%20package%20be%20considered%20NPA%20from%20the%20latest%20date%20and%20not%20from%20the%20date%20prior%20to%20restructuring%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fbanking%2Ffinance%2Fbanking%2Fbanks-reach-out-to-rbi-seek-easing-of-msme-bad-loan-rules%2Farticleshow%2F98923918.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20give%20some%20relief%20to%20banks%20as%20it%20would%20decrease%20their%20provisioning%20burden%2C%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20chief%20advisor%20to%20West%20Bengal%20chief%20minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20finance%20department%2C%20Amit%20Mitra%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.millenniumpost.in%2Fkolkata%2F40k-loan-applications-of-weavers-artisans-denied-amit-mitra-writes-to-fm-504921%5C%22%3Ehad%20written%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20letter%20to%20finance%20minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20saying%20that%20loans%20to%2040%2C000%20highly%20skilled%20weavers%20and%20artisans%20were%20denied%20by%20the%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20sought%20the%20finance%20minister%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20in%20easing%20certain%20stringent%20requirements%20for%20borrowing%20by%20these%20artisans%20and%20weavers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3EFrom%20April%20to%20Sep