-africa-66465146.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%20What%20Is%20Section%20150%2C%20Which%20Will%20Replace%20Sedition%20Law%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre's%20huge%20move%20of%20completely%20overhauling%20criminal%20laws%20in%20India%20also%20has%20a%20provision%20for%20replacing%20the%20colonial-era%20sedition%20law%20with%20Section%20150%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%2C%20which%20deals%20with%20%26quot%3Bacts%20endangering%20sovereignty%2C%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20the%20Law%20Commission%20had%20strongly%20backed%20the%20sedition%20law%20and%20said%20it%20should%20be%20retained%20with%20changes%20linked%20to%20the%20circumstances%20of%20its%20use.%20Repealing%20Section%20124A%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20would%20be%20to%20%26quot%3Bturn%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20the%20glaring%20ground%20realities%20existing%20in%20India%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20Commission%20had%20said%20in%20its%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20the%20Commission%20had%20recommended%20that%20the%20punishment%20for%20sedition%20be%20increased%20from%20three%20years%20in%20jail%20to%20a%20life%20term%20or%20up%20to%20seven%20years%20in%20prison%2C%20which%20has%20been%20implemented%20in%20the%20bill%20introduced%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20by%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20today.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20is%20meant%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20of%201860.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20124A%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20which%20deals%20with%20sedition%2C%20reads%3A%20%26quot%3BWhoever%20by%20words%2C%20either%20spoken%20or%20written%2C%20or%20by%20signs%2C%20or%20by%20visible%20representation%2C%20or%20otherwise%2C%20brings%20or%20attempts%20to%20bring%20into%20hatred%20or%20contempt%2C%20or%20excites%20or%20attempts%20to%20excite%20disaffection%20towards%2C%20the%20Government%20established%20by%20law%20in%20India%2C%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20imprisonment%20for%20life%2C%20to%20which%20fine%20may%20be%20added%2C%20or%20with%20imprisonment%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20three%20years%2C%20to%20which%20fine%20may%20be%20added%2C%20or%20with%20fine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20150%20of%20the%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20is%20longer%20and%20adds%20references%20to%20%26quot%3Bsecession%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3Barmed%20rebellion%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3Bsubversive%20activities%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bseparatist%20activities%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20section%20reads%3A%20%26quot%3BWhoever%2C%20purposely%20or%20knowingly%2C%20by%20words%2C%20either%20spoken%20or%20written%2C%20or%20by%20signs%2C%20or%20by%20visible%20representation%2C%20or%20by%20electronic%20communication%20or%20by%20use%20of%20financial%20means%2C%20or%20otherwise%2C%20excites%20or%20attempts%20to%20excite%2C%20secession%20or%20armed%20rebellion%20or%20subversive%20activities%2C%20or%20encourages%20feelings%20of%20separatist%20activities%20or%20endangers%20sovereignty%20or%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%3B%20or%20indulges%20in%20or%20commits%20any%20such%20act%20shall%20be%20punished%20with%20imprisonment%20for%20life%20or%20with%20imprisonment%20which%20may%20extend%20to%20seven%20years%20and%20shall%20also%20be%20liable%20to%20fine%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20explanation%20for%20Section%20150%20states%2C%20%26quot%3BComments%20expressing%20disapprobation%20of%20the%20measures%2C%20or%20administrative%20or%20other%20action%20of%20the%20Government%20with%20a%20view%20to%20obtain%20their%20alteration%20by%20lawful%20means%20without%20exciting%20or%20attempting%20to%20excite%20the%20activities%20referred%20to%20in%20this%20section.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20explanations%20for%20the%20sedition%20section%20under%20the%20IPC%20read%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20expression%20%26quot%3Bdisaffection%26quot%3B%20includes%20disloyalty%20and%20all%20feelings%20of%20enmity.%20Comments%20expressing%20disapprobation%20of%20the%20measures%20of%20the%20Government%20with%20a%20view%20to%20obtain%20their%20alteration%20by%20lawful%20means%2C%20without%20exciting%20or%20attempting%20to%20excite%20hatred%2C%20contempt%20or%20disaffection%2C%20do%20not%20constitute%20an%20offence%20under%20this%20section.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20explanation%20states%3A%20%26quot%3BComments%20expressing%20disapprobation%20of%20the%20administrative%20or%20other%20action%20of%20the%20Government%20without%20exciting%20or%20attempting%20to%20excite%20hatred%2C%20contempt%20or%20disaffection%2C%20do%20not%20constitute%20an%20offence%20under%20this%20section.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20the%20objective%20is%20to%20replace%20British-era%20laws%2C%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20also%20introduced%20bills%20to%20replace%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20with%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20and%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%20with%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya.%20All%20three%20bills%20have%20been%20referred%20to%20a%20Standing%20Committee.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691747640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-07%2Fatt9hsso_court-generic_625x300_27_July_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-laws-new-criminal-laws-ipc-explained-what-is-section-150-which-will-replace-sedition-law-4289349%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Centre's%20move%20of%20overhauling%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20also%20has%20a%20provision%20for%20replacing%20the%20colonial-era%20sedition%20law%20with%20Section%20150%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%2C%20which%20deals%20with%20%26quot%3Bacts%20endangering%20sovereignty%2C%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnew-laws-new-criminal-laws-ipc-explained-what-is-section-150-which-will-replace-sedition