Ci%3EGadar%3C%2Fi%3E.%20The%20film%20serves%20up%20dollops%20of%20nostalgia%20that%20is%20bolstered%20by%20harking%20back%20to%20two%20of%20the%20original%20film's%20most%20popular%20songs%2C%20%3Ci%3EGhar%20aaja%20pardesi%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20%3Ci%3EMain%20nikla%20gaddi%20leke.%3C%2Fi%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMonty%20Sharma's%20background%20score%20and%20the%20acting%20style%20-%20obstreperous%20and%20melodramatic%20-%20adds%20to%20the%20retro%20feel%20that%20the%20film%20exudes.%20But%20no%20matter%20what%2C%20the%20world%20has%20moved%20on.%20%3Ci%3EGadar%202%3C%2Fi%3E%20appears%20to%20be%20oblivious%20of%20the%20changes%20that%20have%20swept%20away%20much%20of%20what%20once%20defined%20Bollywood%20movies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20strident%20and%20exhausting%20%3Ci%3EGadar%202%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20set%20in%20the%20year%20of%20Bangladesh's%20war%20of%20liberation%2C%20sends%20intrepid%20truck%20driver%20Tara%20Singh%20back%20into%20Pakistan%20to%20rescue%20his%20son%20from%20the%20clutches%20of%20a%20villainous%20Pakistani%20general%20who%20is%20foresworn%20to%20wiping%20India%20off%20the%20face%20of%20the%20earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bad%20guy%20has%20a%20reason%20for%20the%20vitriol%20that%20he%20spews%20-%20his%20parents%20were%20killed%20by%20a%20mob%20in%20the%20Partition%20riots.%20His%20angry%20rhetoric%20turns%20him%20into%20a%20grotesque%20caricature%20deserving%20of%20the%20comeuppance%20that%20he%20is%20going%20to%20receive%20in%20good%20time%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20Sunny%20Deol's%20invincible%20hero.%20Not%20one%20word%20that%20escapes%20the%20man's%20mouth%20sounds%20sane.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETara%20Singh%20launches%20a%20precision%20strike%20inside%20Pakistan%20and%20lands%2C%20in%20the%20nick%20of%20time%20at%20that%2C%20exactly%20where%20his%20son%2C%20Charanjeet%20%26quot%3BJeete%26quot%3B%20Singh%20(Utkarsh%20Sharma%2C%20who%20at%20age%207%20played%20Tara%20Singh%20and%20Sakeena's%20child%20in%20Gadar)%2C%20is%20about%20to%20be%20stoned%20to%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20massive%20crowd%20is%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20lynching%20the%20young%20man%20but%20Tara%20Singh's%20reputation%20as%20the%20slayer%20of%2040%20Pakistani%20soldiers%20back%20in%20the%20immediate%20post-Partition%20years%20precedes%20him.%20His%20advent%20not%20only%20stops%20the%20gathering%20in%20its%20tracks%20but%20also%20allows%20the%20unwelcome%20visitor%20to%20break%20into%20a%20slanging%20match%20with%20General%20Hamid%20Iqbal%20(Manish%20Wadhwa).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fvhwr4vc_GY0%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEverything%20in%20%3Ci%3EGadar%202%3C%2Fi%3E%20is%20exactly%20as%20it%20was%20in%20the%20film%20that%20it%20is%20a%20follow-up%20to.%20The%20Pakistani%20general%20hurls%20a%20challenge%20at%20Tara%20Singh%20that%20harks%20back%20to%20the%20latter's%20handpump-wielding%20avatar%20that%20has%20remained%20etched%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20Hindi%20movie%20fans.%20He%20says%3A%20%26quot%3B%3Ci%3EDekhte%20hain%20aaj%20yeh%20kya%20ukhadta%20hai%3C%2Fi%3E%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20protagonist%20responds%20to%20the%20dare%20with%20befitting%20enthusiasm.%20He%20pulls%20out%20a%20bullock-cast%20wheel%20from%20its%20pivot%20and%20hurls%20it%20at%20his%20foes%20like%20Lord%20Krishna's%20Sudarshan%20chakra%20while%20a%20shloka%20from%20the%20Bhagavad%20Gita%20plays%20on%20the%20soundtrack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETara%20Singh%20follows%20that%20eye-popping%20feat%20up%20with%20a%20couple%20of%20others.%20One%20has%20him%20lifting%20and%20swinging%20a%20massive%20hammer%20in%20the%20manner%20of%20a%20baseball%20bat%20and%20causing%20serious%20damage%20to%20many%20a%20body%20and%20limb.%20He%20then%20uses%20an%20entire%20horse%20carriage%20as%20an%20offensive%20shield%20against%20a%20mob%20of%20attackers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Tara%20Singh%20aims%20hammer%20blows%20at%20the%20men%20in%20his%20way%2C%20his%20dhaai%20kilo%20ka%20haath%20inevitably%20comes%20into%20play%20and%20makes%20the%20weapon%20much%20more%20powerful%20than%20it%20would%20be%20in%20lesser%20hands.%20For%20all%20this%20to%20work%2C%20the%20audience%20has%20to%20be%20in%20tune%20with%20Bollywood%20storytelling%20codes%20of%20an%20era%20long%20gone.%20Those%20that%20can%20manage%20to%20make%20the%20leap%20back%20in%20time%20might%20actually%20enjoy%20parts%20of%20what%20%3Ci%3EGadar%202%3C%2Fi%3E%20has%20on%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20to%20forget%2C%20the%20handpump%20does%20make%20an%20appearance%20in%20the%20film%20but%20stays%20rooted%20to%20the%20ground%20this%20time%20around.%20Much%20water%20has%20flown%20down%20the%20Beas%20and%20Chenab%20in%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20but%20the%20dread%20of%20Tara%20Singh's%20prowess%20still%20persists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWitness%20this%3A%20a%20marauding%20bunch%20of%20bloodthirsty%2C%20sword-wielding%20men%20chases%20him.%20But%20they%20freeze%20when%20they%20spot%20a%20handpump.%20It%20is%20within%20Tara's%20reach%20and%20they%20know%20what%20he%20can%20do%20with%20it.%20He%20does%20not%20even%20have%20to%20pull%20it%20out.%20The%20mob%2C%20suitably%20petrified%2C%20beats%20a%20hasty%20retreat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20action%20high%20points%20are%20all%20reserved%20for%20the%20second%20half.%20The%20first%20half%20of%20the%20nearly%20three-hour%20film%20is%20devoted%20to%20setting%20up%20the%20big%2C%20extended%20showdown%20in%20Lahore%20that%20is%20to%20come.%20Sunny%20Deol%20fills%20up%20the%20screen%2C%20does%20a%20good%20job%20of%20hollering%20and%20hectoring%2C%20be%20it%20in%20anger%20or%20despair%2C%20and%20the%20Pakistanis%20who%20are%20in%20pursuit%20have%20a%20healthy%20respect%20for%20the%20havoc%20that%20the%20one-man%20army%20is%20capable%20of%20wreaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBacktracking%20a%20bit%2C%20as%20the%20war%20clouds%20gather%20in%20the%20border%20area%20where%20Tara%20lives%20with%20his%20wife%20(Ameesha%20Patel)%20and%20his%20son.%20The%20boy%20bunks%20classes%20and%20furtively%20rehearses%20for%20a%20theatre%20production%20of%20Sohni%20Mahiwal.%20His%20heart%20is%20set%20on%20becoming%20a%20movie%20actor.%20His%20father%20will%20have%20none%20of%20it.%20Tempers%20fly%20between%20the%20two%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20skirmish%20erupts%20on%20a%20hill%20that%20separates%20India%20and%20Pakistan.%20Tara%20Singh%20leads%20a%20group%20of%20truckers%20into%20the%20battlefield%20to%20aid%20the%20Indian%20army%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20Colonel%20Devendra%20Rawat%20(Gaurav%20Chopra).%20Eight%20men%2C%20including%20three%20civilians%2C%20are%20captured%20by%20the%20Pakistan%20army.%20Tara%20Singh%20disappears.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESakeena%20is%20distraught.%20Her%20son%20decides%20to%20act.%20Assuming%20a%20fake%20identity%2C%20Jeete%20reaches%20Lahore%20to%20look%20for%20his%20father.%20Another%20love%20story%20begins%20to%20take%20shape%20when%20he%20meets%20Muskaan%20Khan%20(Simrat%20Kaur)%2C%20daughter%20of%20a%20man%20in%20whose%20household%20he%20finds%20employment%20as%20a%20cook.%20Like%20Jeete%2C%20Muskaan%20is%20a%20Hindi%20movie%20enthusiast.%20She%20is%20an%20inveterate%20Rajesh%20Khanna%20fan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20entry%20scene%20is%20heralded%20by%20the%20opening%20riff%20of%20a%20song%20from%20Aradhana.%20Jeete%20plays%20along%20and%20does%20an%20imitation%20of%20a%20cross%20between%20Rajesh%20Khanna%20and%20Dev%20Anand.%20Muskaan%20is%20floored%20by%20his%20charms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEid%20is%20round%20the%20corner.%20The%20girl%20tells%20Jeete%20that%20she%20will%20make%20her%20feelings%20for%20him%20public%20on%20the%20auspicious%20day.%20Jeete%20develops%20cold%20feet%20because%20he%20isn't%20in%20Pakistan%20to%20find%20a%20match%20for%20himself.%20His%20mission%20is%20to%20figure%20out%20where%20his%20father%20is%20and%20take%20him%20back%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20moments%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20intermission%2C%20the%20tables%20turn.%20It%20is%20now%20Tara%20Singh's%20turn%20to%20assume%20the%20mantle%20of%20rescuer.%20Because%20of%20who%20he%20is%2C%20when%20he%20makes%20his%20intentions%20known%2C%20that%20audience%20has%20nothing%20more%20to%20know.%20The%20rest%20of%20%3Ci%3EGadar%202%3C%2Fi%3E%20centres%20on%20the%20adventures%20of%20Tara%20Singh%20and%20his%20son%20in%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EGadar%202%3C%2Fi%3E%20loses%20no%20opportunity%20to%20play%20up%20the%20us-versus-them%20binary%2C%20with%20the%20guys%20across%20the%20border%20generally%20coming%20across%20as%20fiends%20without%20human%20feelings.%20But%20occasionally%2C%20in%20a%20perfunctory%20balancing%20act%2C%20the%20film%20develops%20the%20sense%20to%20throw%20in%20a%20stray%20benefactor%20here%20and%20a%20do-gooder%20there%20as%20the%20father%20and%20son%20pair%20try%20to%20get%20out%20of%20Pakistan%20in%20one%20piece.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EGadar%202%3C%2Fi%3E%20is%20strictly%20for%20three%20categories%20of%20people%3A%20Sunny%20Deol%20fans%2C%20those%20that%20miss%20the%20unbridled%20excesses%20of%20Bollywood%20of%20yore%2C%20and%20those%20that%20believe%20that%20%26quot%3Bhate%20thy%20neighbour%26quot%3B%20is%20an%20axiom%20worth%20cheering%20for%20in%20a%20movie%20theatre.%20The%20film%20has%20enough%20to%20please%20them%20all%20-%20and%20then%20some.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691747460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fvcjt4n3_gadar-2_625x300_11_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fgadar-2-review-strictly-for-sunny-deol-fans-2-stars-4289458%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gadar%202%20Review%3A%20The%20film%20serves%20up%20dollops%20of%20nostalgia%20that%20is%20bolstered%20by%20harking%20back%20to%20two%20of%20the%20original%20film's%20most%20popular%20songs%2C%20Ghar%20aaja%20pardesi%20and%20Main%20nikla%20gaddi%20leke.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%2