%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fnews%2F2023-05-29%2Fnine-pwc-partners-told-to-take-leave-over-tax%2F102408058%3Futm_campaign%3Dabc_news_web%26utm_content%3Dtwitter%26utm_medium%3Dcontent_shared%26utm_source%3Dabc_news_web%5C%22%3EPwC%20is%20under%20intense%20scrutiny%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2Fmay%2F24%2Fpwc-tax-scandal-referred-to-australian-federal-police-for-criminal-investigation%5C%22%3Ealleged%20the%20firm%20misused%20confidential%20government%20tax%20information%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20commercial%20gain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20alleged%20that%2C%20after%20the%20firm%20advised%20the%20government%20on%20tougher%20tax%20laws%2C%20it%20then%20leaked%20the%20design%20of%20those%20laws%20to%20its%20clients%20%E2%80%93%20many%20of%20whom%20would%20be%20targeted%20by%20the%20proposed%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20these%20kinds%20of%20questions%20have%20been%20raised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20recent%20examples%20of%20this%20issue%20being%20explored%20include%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pmc.gov.au%2Fpublications%2Findependent-review-australian-public-service%5C%22%3EThodey%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Australian%20Public%20Service%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.anao.gov.au%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FANAO_Report_2017-2018_19.pdf%5C%22%3E2017%20Australian%20National%20Audit%20Office%3C%2Fa%3E%20audit%20of%20Commonwealth%20departments%E2%80%99%20use%20of%20consultants%20and%20contractors%2C%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.audit.vic.gov.au%2Freport%2Fmanaging-consultants-and-contractors%3Fsection%3D%5C%22%3E2014%20audit%20by%20the%20Victorian%20Auditor-General%E2%80%99s%20Office.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20could%20be%20forgiven%20for%20dismissing%20this%20matter%20as%20an%20insider%20issue%20of%20public%20administration%20best%20left%20to%20the%20boffins%20to%20thrash%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20the%20PwC%20scandal%20illustrates%2C%20the%20excessive%20use%20of%20consultants%20has%20very%20real%20implications%20for%20democratic%20decision-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20many%20experts%20argue%20the%20influx%20of%20consultants%20represents%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FShadow-Government-Governments-Multi-Billion-Dollar-Decision-Making%2Fdp%2F0394492447%5C%22%3Eshadow%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20is%20plundering%20the%20public%20sector.%20Some%20go%20so%20far%20as%20to%20say%20that%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbristoluniversitypressdigital.com%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Fpp%2F35%2F3%2Farticle-p479.xml%5C%22%3Erepresents%20private%20control%20over%20public%20policy.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20therefore%20timely%20to%20consider%20why%20governments%20use%20consultants%20so%20much%2C%20why%20that%20might%20be%20a%20problem%2C%20and%20what%20we%20can%20do%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20consulting%20industry%20can%20be%20traced%20to%20the%20father%20of%20so-called%20%E2%80%98scientific%20management%E2%80%99%2C%20Frederick%20Winslow%20Taylor%2C%20and%20his%20cohort%20of%20%E2%80%98efficiency%20engineers%2C%20which%20included%20such%20business%20luminaries%20as%20Henry%20Gantt%2C%20Lillian%20and%20Frank%20Gilbreth%2C%20and%20Harrington%20Emerson.%20This%20group%20could%20be%20considered%20the%20first%20management%20consultants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20involved%20in%20advising%20the%20United%20States%E2%80%99%20government%20on%20matters%20of%20efficiency%2C%20administration%2C%20or%20organisational%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20Hoover%20Commission%20in%201947%20hired%20two%20consulting%20firms%20to%20provide%20advice%20on%20reforms%20to%20public%20administration.%20Likewise%2C%20political%20scientist%20Denis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.gale.com%2Fapps%2Fdoc%2FA21249108%2FAONE%3Fu%3Dusyd%26sid%3DgoogleScholar%26xid%3D717334af%5C%22%3ESaint-Martin%20has%20described%20the%201960%20Canadian%20Glassco%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20Government%20Reorganisation%20as%20%E2%80%98by%20far%20the%20most%20impressive%20demonstration%20of%20the%20influence%20of%20consultants%20in%20government%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsultants%20received%20a%20massive%20%E2%80%98shot%20in%20the%20arm%E2%80%99%20through%20the%20introduction%20of%20a%20bundle%20of%20reforms%20collectively%20known%20as%20the%20new%20public%20management.%20This%20introduced%20into%20government%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%E2%80%98Hands%20on%E2%80%99%20professional%20public%20management%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EExplicit%20performance%20measures%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEmphasis%20on%20%E2%80%98output%20controls%E2%80%99%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECompetition%20in%20the%20public%20sector%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDisaggregation%20of%20units%20in%20the%20public%20sector%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EStress%20on%20private%20sector%20styles%20of%20management%20practice.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20its%20introduction%2C%20spending%20on%20consultants%20increased%20dramatically.%20In%20the%20UK%2C%20spending%20on%20consultants%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Defence%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2Fj.1467-6281.2009.00275.x%5C%22%3Efrom%201993%20to%202006%3C%2Fa%3E%20increased%20from%20%C2%A355%20million%20to%20%C2%A3256%20million.%20Over%20the%20same%20period%2C%20spending%20by%20the%20Home%20Office%20increased%20from%20%C2%A33.81%20million%20to%20%C2%A3125%20million%20%E2%80%93%20a%20change%20of%203%2C190%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20public%20management%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%201980s%20when%20the%20economic%20ideas%20of%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%20Margaret%20Thatcher%20and%20US%20President%20Ronald%20Reagan%20held%20sway.%20It%20represented%20a%20victory%20of%20private%20sector%20ideology%20over%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F11135620%2F1024px-President_Ronald_Reagan_and_Prime_Minister_Margaret_Thatcher_of_the_United_Kingdom.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F11135620%2F1024px-President_Ronald_Reagan_and_Prime_Minister_Margaret_Thatcher_of_the_United_Kingdom.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F11135620%2F1024px-President_Ronald_Reagan_and_Prime_Minister_Margaret_Thatcher_of_the_United_Kingdom-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667641%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22679%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERonald%20Reagan%20with%20Margaret%20Thatcher.%20Photo%3A%20Unknown%20photographer%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20Public%20domain%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20underlying%20logic%20was%20that%20the%20private%20sector%20knows%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrivate%20sector%20management%20techniques%20were%20hypothetically%20introduced%20to%20produce%20better%20public%20sector%20outcomes.%20Whether%20new%20public%20management%20has%20done%20this%20or%20not%20remains%20a%20heated%20point%20of%20debate.%20At%20the%20very%20least%2C%20it%20has%20created%20an%20environment%20in%20which%20consultants%20can%20thrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20also%20been%20a%20major%20contributor%20to%20the%20loss%20of%20expertise%20in%20government.%20As%20Professor%20Rod%20Rhodes%20described%20it%20many%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20state%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1111%2Fj.1467-923X.1994.tb00441.x%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98hollowed%20out%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20governments%20have%20turned%20to%20consultants%20more.%20However%2C%20this%20meant%20that%20public%20servants%20were%20not%20doing%20the%20necessary%20work%20to%20upgrade%20their%20skills%20and%20increase%20their%20expertise.%20The%20consultants%20were%20gaining%20that%20expertise%20and%20%E2%80%93%20for%20a%20fee%20%E2%80%93%20providing%20their%20advice%20to%20bureaucrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReliance%20on%20consultants%20became%20more%20and%20more%20entrenched%2C%20so%20now%20we%20are%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20consultants%20are%20seen%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98shadow%E2%80%99%20public%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20presence%20of%20consultants%20on%20its%20own%20is%20not%20a%20problem.%20Decision%20makers%20throughout%20the%20ages%20have%20turned%20to%20advisors%20to%20assist%20with%20pressing%20challenges.%20Besides%2C%20the%20nature%20of%20governing%20today%20is%20far%20more%20complex%20than%20it%20was%20even%20a%20few%20decades%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20prudent%2C%20therefore%2C%20to%20turn%20to%20a%20range%20of%20different%20sources%20for%20advice%20%E2%80%93%20including%20consultants.%20And%20there%20are%20situations%20where%20very%20highly%20specialised%20or%20technical%20knowledge%20is%20required%20to%20support%20public%20decision-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20principle%20of%20consultants%20being%20part%20of%20governing%20today%20is%20sound%2C%20it%20is%20the%20practice%20that%20is%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20four%20parts%20to%20this%20problem%3A%20definition%2C%20quantity%2C%20management%20and%20procurement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20of%20definition%20relates%20to%20the%20public%20sector%E2%80%99s%20understanding%20of%20what%20consultants%20are%20and%20what%20they%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20confusion%20as%20to%20how%20consultants%20differ%20from%20contractors%20and%2C%20as%20a%20result%2C%20how%20best%20to%20deploy%20them.%20This%20issue%20is%20fundamental%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20work%20that%20consultants%20are%20asked%20to%20do%20and%20how%20governments%20report%20on%20the%20extent%20of%20consultancy%20spending%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20means%20work%20more%20appropriately%20classified%20as%20a%20contractor%20can%20be%20recorded%20as%20a%20consultancy%20(and%20vice-versa).%20It%20also%20means%20departments%20can%20pay%20a%20premium%20for%20the%20services%20of%20a%20consultant%20when%20a%20(much%20cheaper)%20contractor%20would%20suffice.%20It%20also%20might%20result%20in%20contractors%20putting%20up%20sub-standard%20work%2C%20thereby%20damaging%20the%20reputation%20of%20consultants%20generally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20of%20quantity%20relates%20to%20how%20often%20governments%20use%20consultants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Victorian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.audit.vic.gov.au%2Fdashboards%2Fdepartments-reported-consultant-spend-2017-18-2021-22%5C%22%3EAuditor-General%E2%80%99s%20Office%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20estimated%20that%20the%20current%20Labor%20Government%20has%20spent%20(on%20average)%20AUD%24140%20million%20on%20consultants%20each%20year%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years.%20If%20we%20assume%20that%20the%20average%20cost%20of%20a%20consulting%20project%20is%20AUD%24100%2C000%2C%20then%20that%20is%201%2C400%20consulting%20projects%20across%20the%20state%20government%20%E2%80%94%20roughly%20140%20per%20department%20per%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20large%2C%20this%20pales%20in%20comparison%20to%20the%20United%20Kingdom%E2%80%99s%20spend%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2Ffeb%2F06%2Fministers-quietly-scrap-limits-on-whitehall-spending-on-consultants%5C%22%3E%C2%A32.8%20billion%20worth%20of%20consulting%20work%20in%202022%20alone.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20of%20quantity%20is%20not%20just%20about%20%E2%80%98how%20much%E2%80%99.%20It%20is%20also%20about%20%E2%80%98who%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bulk%20of%20consulting%20work%20is%20often%20awarded%20to%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%98Big%20Four%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20KPMG%2C%20Deloitte%2C%20PwC%20and%20Ernst%20%26amp%3B%20Young.%20The%20sheer%20volume%20of%20work%2C%20compounded%20with%20the%20awarding%20of%20work%20to%20a%20select%20group%20of%20firms%2C%20suggests%20the%20government%20is%20dependent%20on%20these%20specific%20firms.%20One%20UK%20official%20even%20warned%20others%20about%20getting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F00076790500055756%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98addicted%20to%20having%20well%20trained%2C%20hard%20working%20people%20running%20around%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20management%20problem%20relates%20to%20poor%20supervision%20of%20consultants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDepartment%20officials%20sometimes%20see%20consulting%20work%20as%20%E2%80%98set-and-forget%E2%80%99%2C%20meaning%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20actively%20manage%20or%20take%20ownership%20of%20the%20process%20or%20the%20results.%20This%20may%20result%20in%20something%20that%20is%20not%20fit%20for%20purpose%2C%20meaning%20additional%20spending%20might%20be%20necessary%20to%20rectify%20a%20report%20or%20unwanted%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsultants%20can%20often%20be%20put%20in%20a%20position%20of%20power%20over%20their%20clients%20where%20the%20client%20does%20not%20necessarily%20understand%20the%20work%20the%20consultant%20is%20doing.%20Ideally%2C%20a%20consulting%20project%20should%20be%20co-owned%20by%20the%20bureaucrat%20and%20the%20consultant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20here%20is%20that%20bureaucrats%20end%20up%20defaulting%20to%20a%20consultant%20when%20internal%20staff%20might%20be%20more%20than%20capable%20of%20doing%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvpsc.vic.gov.au%2Fdata-and-research%2Fdata-facts-visuals-state-of-the-sector%2Femployment-arrangements-pay-grades-occupations%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20insecurity%20of%20public%20sector%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20sometimes%20mean%20consultants%20themselves%20become%20the%20keeper%20of%20institutional%20memory.%20If%20the%20right%20structures%20aren%E2%80%99t%20put%20in%20place%2C%20this%20can%20mean%20the%20expertise%20of%20the%20public%20sector%20is%20further%20eroded%20and%20the%20presence%20of%20consultants%20is%20made%20more%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20there%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F09540962.2023.2184273%3FjournalCode%3Drpmm20%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAs%2520part%2520of%2520this%252C%2520we%2Cdynamics%2520are%2520maintained%2520and%2520expressed.%5C%22%3Eproblem%20of%20procurement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20traditional%20model%20assumes%20consulting%20services%20can%20be%20purchased%20just%20like%20any%20other%20good.%20However%2C%20the%20reality%20of%20purchasing%20consulting%20services%20is%20very%20different%20from%2C%20say%2C%20purchasing%20a%20piece%20of%20infrastructure.%20Consultants%20are%20often%20in%20relationships%20of%20co-dependency%20with%20government%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20relationships%20transcend%20individual%20transactions.%20However%2C%20the%20way%20in%20which%20procurement%20is%20practised%20often%20disguises%20these%20relationships%2C%20thus%20creating%20challenges%20in%20holding%20consultants%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccountability%20issues%20are%20further%20compounded%20given%20that%20consultants%20can%20often%20hide%20behind%20commercial-in-confidence%20privileges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20address%20this%20issue%20we%20first%20need%20to%20rebuild%20the%20policy%20capacity%20of%20the%20public%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsultants%20should%20only%20be%20called%20in%20when%20a%20task%20requires%20a%20highly%20specialised%20form%20of%20knowledge%20combined%20with%20a%20deep%20understanding%20of%2C%20and%20relationships%20with%2C%20the%20specific%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20short%20term%2C%20consultants%20could%20be%20required%20to%20upskill%20the%20public%20service%20in%20their%20processes%20and%20methodologies.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fminerva-access.unimelb.edu.au%2Fitems%2F31f5b92a-27b1-5dec-9e6c-ba2435c92fd9%5C%22%3EAs%20this%20research%20demonstrated%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20does%20happen%2C%20though%20it%20might%20not%20be%20common%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternal%20consulting%20divisions%20within%20the%20government%20are%20a%20possibility.%20Interestingly%2C%20Australia%E2%80%99s%20current%20Labor%20Government%20has%20committed%20to%20doing%20just%20that%20at%20the%20same%20time%20as%20the%20UK%20Cabinet%20Office%20is%20shutting%20its%20down%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20effectiveness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20real%20piece%20of%20work%20is%20long-term%20generational%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20career%20path%20for%20public%20servants%20and%20considering%20policy%20work%20a%20genuine%20profession%20can%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20involve%20better%20links%20between%20the%20public%20service%20and%20universities.%20It%20could%20see%20public%20departments%20define%20workforce%20needs%20and%20talk%20to%20universities%20directly%20about%20how%20those%20needs%20can%20be%20filled.%20It%20could%20consider%20public%20policy%20knowledge%20a%20genuine%20form%20of%20professional%20knowledge%20in%20its%20own%20right%20%E2%80%93%20similar%20to%20law%20or%20accounting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20going%20to%20require%20several%20years%20to%20get%20right.%20Largely%20because%20Australia%20is%20now%20trying%20to%20wind%20back%20several%20decades%20of%20neoliberal%20ideology%20%E2%80%93%20not%20something%20that%20can%20be%20done%20overnight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPublic%20servants%20could%20be%20trained%20in%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20work%20with%20consultants.%20On%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20consultants%20who%20want%20to%20work%20in%20government%20services%20could%20be%20required%20to%20undertake%20a%20professional%20accreditation%20that%20demonstrates%20they%20understand%20the%20important%20contextual%20differences%20between%20the%20public%20and%20private%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20procurement%20rules%20can%20be%20updated%20to%20remove%20the%20category%20of%20%E2%80%98consulting%E2%80%99%20altogether.%20It%20causes%20too%20much%20confusion.%20Rather%2C%20categories%20could%20be%20based%20on%20the%20type%20of%20expertise%20that%20is%20actually%20being%20purchased.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20governments%20often%20purchase%20evaluation%20services%2C%20but%20%E2%80%98evaluation%E2%80%99%20is%20not%20a%20recognised%20category%20in%20AusTender.%20Likewise%2C%20strategy%20advice%20or%20analytics%20are%20commonly-provided%20consulting%20services%20but%20are%20typically%20subsumed%20under%20the%20much%20broader%20category%20of%20%E2%80%98Management%20and%20Business%20Professionals%20and%20Administrative%20Services%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20very%20high-level%20categories%20can%20obscure%20as%20much%20as%20they%20reveal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20approach%20to%20procurement%20and%20the%20procurement%20rules%20applicable%20to%20consultants%20could%20also%20be%20overhauled%20to%20recognise%20the%20fundamentally%20relational%20%E2%80%93%20not%20transactional%20%E2%80%93%20ways%20in%20which%20consultants%20enter%20the%20public%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForms%20of%20%E2%80%98relational%20contracting%E2%80%99%20would%20be%20investigated%20to%20allow%20for%20more%20transparency%20in%20the%20ways%20consultants%20are%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsultancies%20could%20be%20subject%20to%20a%20set%20of%20ethical%20rules%20and%20professional%20standards.%20Consulting%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20%E2%80%98look%20like%E2%80%99%20any%20other%20profession.%20There%20is%20no%20academic%20qualification%2C%20no%20professional%20standards%2C%20and%20no%20regulatory%20body%20for%20the%20profession.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20anybody%20can%20set%20up%20shop%20and%20call%20themselves%20a%20consultant.%20Addressing%20this%20issue%20would%20go%20a%20long%20way%20to%20ensuring%20money%20is%20spent%20appropriately%20and%20is%20providing%20quality%20outcomes%20to%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20role%20for%20consultants%20to%20play%20in%20modern%20systems%20of%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20a%20lot%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20to%20ensure%20that%20we%20can%20rein%20in%20some%20of%20the%20excessive%20public%20expenditure%20on%20private%20forms%20of%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20several%20ideas%20that%20could%20be%20implemented%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20the%20real%20%E2%80%98fix%E2%80%99%20is%20moving%20away%20from%20ideologically%20privileging%20the%20private%20sector%20to%20recognise%20the%20unique%20value%20that%20public%20policy%20analysis%20and%20public%20servants%20can%20provide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20a%20structural%20reform%20but%20a%20shift%20in%20perspective%20and%20culture.%20We%20can%E2%80%99t%20unscramble%20the%20omelette%2C%20but%20we%20can%20certainly%20make%20it%20taste%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EDr%20Marty%20Bortz%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3Eis%20an%20Honorary%20Senior%20Fellow%20at%20the%20Melbourne%20School%20of%20Government%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Melbourne.%20He%20has%20worked%20in%20local%20and%20state%20government%2C%20and%20private%20consulting%2C%20across%20multiple%20portfolios%20including%20education%2C%20health%2C%20justice%20and%20Indigenous%20affairs.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOriginally%20published%20under%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20by%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E360info%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691742544000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F11134930%2Fadriano-hhkJV1mbxw-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22h