a%20high%20court%20on%20Thursday%20(August%2010)%20stayed%20an%20order%20passed%20by%20a%20single-judge%20bench%20imposing%20a%20cost%20of%20Rs%2050%20lakh%20on%20X%20Corp%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20for%20allegedly%20not%20complying%20with%20the%20IT%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20orders.%20However%2C%20the%20stay%20will%20only%20be%20in%20place%20if%20the%20company%20deposits%2050%25%20of%20the%20amount%20%E2%80%93%20or%20Rs%2025%20lakh%20%E2%80%93%20within%20one%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20such%2C%20on%20deposit%20of%C2%A0%3Cspan%3E%E2%82%B9%3C%2Fspan%3E25%20lakh%2C%20the%20order%20of%20the%20single%20judge%20bench%20is%20stayed%20until%20the%20next%20hearing%20date%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20high%20court%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fbengaluru-news%2Fkarnataka-hc-stays-order-imposing-rs-50-lakh-cost-on-x-corp-for-non-compliance-with-it-ministry-orders-101691721758613.html%5C%22%3EPTI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20court%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20asking%20the%20company%20to%20deposit%20the%20amount%20should%20not%20be%20treated%20as%20an%20acceptance%20by%20the%20court%20that%20Twitter%20has%20a%20case%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneycontrol.com%2Fnews%2Ftrends%2Flegal%2Fx-corp-vs-govt-case-karnataka-hc-asks-company-to-deposit-25-lakhs-as-bonafide-11140391.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMoneycontrol%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20earlier%20court%20order%20passed%20by%20the%20single-judge%20bench%20had%20held%20that%20Twitter%20did%20not%20comply%20with%20the%20IT%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20orders%20for%20over%20a%20year%20and%20then%20approached%20the%20court%20against%20the%20orders.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20orders%20sought%20the%20blocking%20of%201%2C474%20accounts%2C%20175%20tweets%2C%20256%20URLs%20and%20one%20hashtag%20on%20Twitter.%20On%20Thursday%20too%2C%20the%20high%20court%20noted%20that%20Twitter%20had%20done%20nothing%20about%20the%20orders%20until%20the%20govern